	<h2 class="title"><P>City Languages Forum</P></h2>

				<a name="BodyText1"></a>
			
		<span id="blacktext">
			<P>The City&nbsp;Languages Forum helps to promote the <A href="/downloads/education/education_online/key_documents/your_community/city_languages_forum/citylangstrat_finalv1.doc">Brighton &amp; Hove Languages Strategy</A>.</P>
<P>Forum&nbsp;<A href="/downloads/education/education/education_extras/forummembershipapr04.doc">members</A> are drawn from across the spectrum of organisations providing language teaching or concerned with language skills in Brighton &amp; Hove.&nbsp; The Forum meets around 6&nbsp;times a year to facilitate exchange of information, views, and&nbsp;innovative&nbsp;collaborations between the member organisations. The Chair is currently held by the Director of Children, Families &amp; Schools.&nbsp;&nbsp;</P>
<P>There is no charge to be included on the Forum circulation list and invited to meetings. For further information please email <A href="mailto:viki.junor@brighton-hove.gov.uk">viki.junor@brighton-hove.gov.uk</A> </P>
